burn(address).details: In the case of malicious or erroneous node operator behavior, this function can be used by Telcoin governance to eject a validator from consensus and burn their `ConsensusNFT`

params.from: Refers to the struct member `ValidatorInfo.ecdsaPubkey` in `IConsensusRegistry`

claimStakeRewards().details: Used for validators to claim their staking rewards for validating the network

concludeEpoch(address[]).details: Accepts the committee of voting validators for 2 epochs in the future

params.newCommittee: The future validator committee for 2 epochs after  the current one is finalized; ie `$.currentEpoch + 3` (this func increments `currentEpoch`)

exit().details: Issues an exit request for a validator to be ejected from the active validator set

getEpochInfo(uint32).details: Returns information about the provided epoch. Only four latest & two future epochs are stored

getRewards(address).details: Fetches the claimable rewards accrued for a given validator address

returns.claimableRewards: The validator's claimable rewards, not including the validator's stake

getValidatorByIndex(uint24).details: Fetches the `ValidatorInfo` for a given validator index

getValidatorIndex(address).details: Fetches the `validatorIndex` for a given validator address

getValidators(uint8).details: Returns an array of `ValidatorInfo` structs that match the provided status for this epoch

incrementRewards((uint24,uint240)[]).details: Increments the claimable rewards for each validator

params.stakingRewardInfos: Staking reward info defining which validators to reward and how much each rewardee earned for the current epoch

params.initialValidators_: The initial validator set running Telcoin Network; these validators will comprise the voter committee for the first three epochs, ie `epochInfo[0:2]`

mint(address,uint256).details: The StakeManager's ERC721 ledger serves a permissioning role over validators, requiring Telcoin governance to approve each node operator and manually issue them a `ConsensusNFT`

params.to: Refers to the struct member `ValidatorInfo.ecdsaPubkey` in `IConsensusRegistry`

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Emergency function to pause validator and stake management

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

rejoin(bytes,bytes32).details: Issues a rejoin request for an exited validator to reactivate

params.blsPubkey: Callers may provide a new BLS key if they wish to update it
params.ed25519Pubkey: Callers may provide a new ED25519 key if they wish to update it

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

stake(bytes,bytes,bytes32).details: Accepts the stake amount of native TEL and issues an activation request for the caller (validator)

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Emergency function to unpause validator and stake management

unstake().details: Returns previously staked funds and accrued rewards, if any, to the calling validator

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

burn(address).notice: The ERC721 `tokenId` corresponds to ConsensusRegistry's validator indexAccess-gated in ConsensusRegistry to its owner, which is a Telcoin governance address

claimStakeRewards().notice: Rewards are incremented every epoch via syscall in `concludeEpoch()`

concludeEpoch(address[]).notice: Voting Validator Committee changes once every epoch (== 32 rounds)Can only be called in a `syscall` context, at the end of an epoch

exit().notice: Reverts if the caller would cause the network to lose BFT by exitingCaller must be a validator with `ValidatorStatus.Active` status

getEpochInfo(uint32).notice: When querying for future epochs, `blockHeight` will be 0 as they are not yet known

getRewards(address).notice: Does not include the original stake amount and cannot be claimed until surpassing `minWithdrawAmount`

getValidatorByIndex(uint24).notice: To enable checks against storage slots initialized to zero by the EVM, `validatorIndex` cannot be `0`

getValidatorIndex(address).notice: A returned `validatorIndex` value of `0` is invalid and indicates that the given address is not a known validator's ECDSA externalkey

incrementRewards((uint24,uint240)[]).notice: May only be called by the client via system call, at the start of a new epoch

initialize(address,uint256,uint256,(byte.notice: Not actually used since this contract is precompiled and written to TN at genesis It is left in the contract for readable information about the relevant storage slots at genesis

mint(address,uint256).notice: To match ConsensusRegistry's validator index, `tokenId` cannot exceed `type(uint24).max`Access-gated in ConsensusRegistry to its owner, which is a Telcoin governance address

pause().notice: Does not pause `concludeEpoch()`. Only accessible by `owner`

rejoin(bytes,bytes32).notice: Caller must be a validator with `ValidatorStatus.Exited` status

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.notice: Consensus NFTs are soulbound to validators that mint them and cannot be transfered

stake(bytes,bytes,bytes32).notice: Caller must already have been issued a `ConsensusNFT` by Telcoin governance

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Consensus NFTs are soulbound to validators that mint them and cannot be transfered

unpause().notice: Does not affect `concludeEpoch()`. Only accessible by `owner`

unstake().notice: May only be called after fully exiting
